This paper discusses a machine learning algorithm that combines different optimization techniques to improve performance in various environments. The paper's focus on optimization and machine learning suggests that it is likely to belong to the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the use of MuJoCo environments suggests a potential connection to robotics and control, which could place it in the category of cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also mentions the use of natural gradients, which are commonly used in computer vision, placing it in the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the use of neural networks and optimization techniques suggests a potential connection to neural engineering, placing it in the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
